<br>
ie. Enter from Echo, follow leftmost path (is that the only path?) along the buildings and gates, then run through one tunnel that has a guard patrolling it. At the end of the tunnel is a shroom patch that has (I think) 6 shrooms. When you exit the tunnel there will be one of those plant guys to your immediate left. To the right is a tarnok village.<br>
<br>
I forgot to mention that I tried not using a healer there (she died from the plant surprise-nuking her at one point, so I left her at Nexus for a bit). Of course, the XP is a bit slower, and there may be a bit of downtime involved (like 30 seconds between mobs), but religious use of mod rods helps. I didn't try a full hour of soloing without the healer, but I would say that 8 to 9% (versus 12% with) per hour should be possible.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 436<br> <font color=#333333>(2/14/03 3:58:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=356.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: First Patch</span><hr size=1> I don't see how you managed 25% regular xp per two hours then... there's just not enough shrooms in that camp to keep you busy.<br>
