<br>
If you send in the pet before the shroom gets to you, you should never be touched by the shroom. So, it's more or less irrelevant whether a slow spell or shroom morph/root spell sticks on you. The only exception is that if things somehow screw up and the shroom roots you within its melee range. Then you're in deep trouble.<br>
<br>
However, if you don't try to sit down before the pet sticks root onto the shroom and gets aggro, you should never run into this problem. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=outofmana>OutOfMana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 4:27:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=356.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Focus the Pet</span><hr size=1> /em confused.<br>
